✨
Happy National Dog Day to my 3 furry sons❣️
Dogs are humans in our family and are treated as such.
They are spoiled, pampered, they get groomed and manicured regularly, hot dinner every night, and celebrate their birthdays.
How do you not spoil these wonderful creatures who are nothing but unconditional love 24/7?!?!
If I could take in 1,000 more and give them loving homes, I would, but I think Van would maybe make me sleep outside if I allow one more into our bed LOL 😂 
If you’re on the fence about getting a dog — DO IT!  There are too many in shelters, especially high kill shelters that need loving homes and are desperate to not be euthanized.
I’m such a softy for these furry friends that every time I see a sad puppy post online, I instantly burst into tears and I just wish I could save them all.  Also cry when one of my friend’s dogs gets sick or dies.
And I’m NOT a crier LOL usually a stone cold ice Queen 👸🥶😂
But sad puppy stories just BREAK ME! 😫
Anyways, today I’m celebrating these 3 goonie birds who spend their days constantly chasing each other, wrestling, and their nights snuggling us and snoring.
They are the 3 best friends that anyone could have.
Monstro can open doorknobs, sliding glass door latches, reach anything, and scare the neighbors over the 10 foot backyard fence like Clifford.
Odin can lock himself in any bathroom and then panic, unplug my charges 5x a day by consistently tripping over them, and likes to bark at the water hose because it is definitely an evil killing device.
Puppito can chew any material dog bed, any expensive workout shoe, and through any bone hard as a rock, and also doubles as a nice height foot stool.
But despite their weird qualities, Monstro acts like the most lovable gentle-giant human child, Puppito is partial to McKenna and acts like her little baby, and Odin gets along amazing with everyone and is the most chill dog ever. 99.9% of the time they are so well behaved and angels thankfully at this age.
I love them to pieces and I’m so glad I’m home with them every day because 7-15 human years is just NOT ENOUGH when they give unconditional love and you love them this much. 😭😭
I LOVE YOU MY SWEET BABIES❣️

Happy Mother’s Day to all the mommies and grandmas out there!
✨
April 2012, I adopted my first dog who will always be my 1st baby, Bull.
June 2012, I graduated college.
September 2012, just 3 months after I graduated, I conceived my first human child lol, my daughter McKenna.
July 2013 I became a mommy.
✨
Thanks to these two precious souls for making me a mommy and teaching me true unconditional love.
Here is our first year together — the 12 months that forever changed my life for the better in every way, shape, and form. ❤️❣️
You two gave/give me strength in absolutely everything I do. You taught me I could do anything and overcome everything. You brought joy to my days and excitement to my nights. I would never choose anything different than the journey we have had. I ride for you. I fight for you. I’d die for you. 
You have taught me strength in every sense of the word. There’s nothing I won’t do for you, there’s no mountain I won’t climb, and no one will ever come between us.
Everything I have, do, and am, is because of you.
I am unstoppable because of you.
I owe it all to you (and God).

✨
Merry Christmas everyone! 🎄🎅🏻⛄️🎁❄️
I hope your day was filled with love & joy, family & friends❣️
✨
Every year I go ALL OUT creating a Winter Wonderland in our home.  Anyone who knows me knows that I’m OBSESSED with decorating for Christmas & making it a magical place for our family to celebrate the birth of Jesus. ✝️
The funny thing is, my sister in Kentucky is equally fanatical about decorating for Christmas, & she actually starts MONTHS ahead of time which totally cracks me up. 🤣
I usually start decorating on the 1st of December, but got started a few days later this year.  Our family tradition going back generations on my Italian father’s side is to leave up our decorations until 1/6 (which is The Epiphany or “La Befana” a national Christmas holiday in Italy) & also happens to be my birthday 🥳🎉🎊🎈🎁 so we have another 2 weeks of enjoying the festive decorations before they come down, which I absolutely love! 😍🥰
✨
Having a space filled with lights, glitter, sentimental trinkets, cards, photos, & memories always gets McKenna & I in the spirit — she looks forward to helping me decorate every year, & this year being 7, had a lot to say about where things should go — so cute!
✨
I hope you all enjoyed your Christmas & you got to nurture the artistic side of your brain by doing a little decorative creating, whether it was your home, your tree, a gingerbread house, candles, or whatever other traditions you enjoy! ❤️
✨

✨
Happy 3rd Birthday to my baby boy Monstro & 4th Birthday to my big boy Odin 🐶🐶❣️
Born during the month of Christmas, they truly are both a precious gift 💝 
✨
They are best friends, brothers, & inseparable.  I’ve never seen two dogs wrestle 24/7, play all day, & love each other so much.
From the day Monstro came home, he was attached at Odin’s hip, & when he quickly outgrew him, he made sure to be extra gentle with him & never hurt him during their multiple daily hour-long wrestling matches.
They eat together, sleep together, go to the groomers together... you can’t ever find them apart.  Watching their bond grow over the years has been simply amazing, with lots of laughs at their ridiculous play full speed gallops in the backyard & dive bombing each other for fun.
✨
Birthday steak, some candles, & a giant new stuffy made these boys feel extra special & celebrated.
Watch til the end so you can see them passed out after an epic birthday... they both partied too hard.
✨
I’m so grateful to have these two in my life.  Dogs really do show you unconditional love, & anyone who knows me, knows how obsessed I am with them.  They will forever have a special place in my heart as my fur babies.
✨
This is a big year for them, as there have been a lot of changes, & for Christmas they get a new little brother. 🐶
✨

HAPPY 2ND BIRTHDAY PUPPITO!!!
😘🥳🎂🎊🎉🎁🎈🎊🎉🎁
✨
You are my sweet and mischievous littlest boy and I love you so much❣️
✨
You love to chew anything and everything, love to cuddle in our big bed when Daddy pulls you up because you’re too short and stumpy and fat to jump on your own, and you were the perfect addition to our little dog family to complete it. 🐶🐶🐶
You chase your two big brothers all day long, and the three of you guys are literally the Three Stooges! Always running around and acting absolutely hilarious. You guys give me more laughs than anything on TV!
Between having so much fun wrestling all day in the backyard together, to snuggling each other at night, your brotherly dog bond just warms my heart!
I don’t care what people say — DOGS ARE PEOPLE TOO❣️❣️❣️
And since they live only a quarter of the time, they totally deserve birthday parties!!! 🎁🎈
✨
This video captures their hilarious nature perfectly …

Happy National Dog Day to my 3 furry sons❣️
Dogs are humans in our family and are treated as such.
They are spoiled, pampered, they get groomed and manicured regularly, hot dinner every night, and celebrate their birthdays.
How do you not spoil these wonderful creatures who are nothing but unconditional love 24/7?!?!
If I could take in 1,000 more and give them loving homes, I would, but I think Van would maybe make me sleep outside if I allow one more into our bed LOL 😂 
If you’re on the fence about getting a dog — DO IT!  There are too many in shelters, especially high kill shelters that need loving homes and are desperate to not be euthanized.
I’m such a softy for these furry friends that every time I see a sad puppy post online, I instantly burst into tears and I just wish I could save them all.  Also cry when one of my friend’s dogs gets sick or dies.
And I’m NOT a crier LOL usually a stone cold ice Queen 👸🥶😂
But sad puppy stories just BREAK ME! 😫
Anyways, today I’m celebrating these 3 goonie birds who spend their days constantly chasing each other, wrestling, and their nights snuggling us and snoring.
They are the 3 best friends that anyone could have.
Monstro can open doorknobs, sliding glass door latches, reach anything, and scare the neighbors over the 10 foot backyard fence like Clifford.
Odin can lock himself in any bathroom and then panic, unplug my charges 5x a day by consistently tripping over them, and likes to bark at the water hose because it is definitely an evil killing device.
Puppito can chew any material dog bed, any expensive workout shoe, and through any bone hard as a rock, and also doubles as a nice height foot stool.
But despite their weird qualities, Monstro acts like the most lovable gentle-giant human child, Puppito is partial to McKenna and acts like her little baby, and Odin gets along amazing with everyone and is the most chill dog ever. 99.9% of the time they are so well behaved and angels thankfully at this age.
I love them to pieces and I’m so glad I’m home with them every day because 7-15 human years is just NOT ENOUGH when they give unconditional love and you love them this much. 😭😭
I LOVE YOU MY SWEET BABIES❣️
